rComments: Overall this class was easy however the assignment instructions were always very unclear. You needed to sift through the information giving to figure out exactly what she wanted. She goes off on a lot of tangents during the lectures that don't really have to do with the course content.

Midterms seemed like the fairly common formula: MC questions from textbook (some quite tricky), long-answer from lecture notes. Yes she goes off on tangents, but it was a dry subject material that she made somewhat bearable. For her assignments, try to cover everything from her lecture notes and some textbook concepts to get a decent mark on them.

Assignment instructions are unclear and it's hard to tell what is expected, only gives instructions a week in advance. Midterms and final are decent. She is extremely dramatic and outgoing and I often got annoyed by her constant effort to make jokes and referring to herself as a "nerd". She is a nice person though and eager to answer questions

The type of professor you'd like to have a conversation with, but not have as an instructor. She takes 10 minutes to answer simple questions. Teaches the course in a very 'broad understanding' way,  but the midterms were very detail specific. Assignment instructions sometimes vague. TA was a challenging marker. Course textbook is poor. prof is hot
